JOHANNESBURG – Spanish giants Barcelona are to jet into South Africa to face Mamelodi Sundowns. The Absa Premiership champions confirmed that they will host the Spanish champions at FNB Stadium on 16 May. READ: 'Very sad' Wenger laments missed chances for Arsenal It will be the second time Bafana Ba Style host Barcelona. In 2007, the Catalans prevailed 2-1 in a clash played at Loftus Versfeld Stadium in Pretoria. eNCA